          "candidate_value": "Your funds could also be on hold because of a recent deposit that exceeds your Access to Funds limit.",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-4e331544af55c5ff",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "mply select Manage My Card on your Credit Card Details page and follow the steps to use the Replace Lost or Stolen Card feature.\nYour funds could also be on hold because of a recent deposit that exceeds your Access to Funds limit.\nYour Access to Funds limit is the amount of funds available to you right away when you make a deposit. This limit is set when the account is opened.\nYou agree to be responsible for any negotiable item (cheque, draft, money order) that you deposit into your bank account based on the terms of\u00a0 the account agreement in effect from time to time in relation to your account. Any hold placed on the portion of your deposit that isn\u2019t immediately made available to you provides you with a measure of protection. The hold period is designed to account for the time it takes for most negotiable items to clear back to the bank they are drawn on. When the hold expires, this",
